.TH FBC-ANDROID 1 "2026-04-29" "FreeBASIC Compiler" "FreeBASIC Compiler"
.SH NAME
fbc-android \- FreeBASIC compiler driver for Android APKs
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B fbc-android
[\fIoptions\fR] \fIprogram.bas\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B fbc-android
builds a FreeBASIC source file using the packaged Android target runtime and
produces a signed debug APK by default.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --emit-apk
Produce a signed debug APK. This is the default.
.TP
.B --emit-so
Produce only the native shared library.
.TP
.B --emit-obj
Produce only the compiled FreeBASIC object file.
.TP
.BI --api " N"
Use Android NDK API level
.IR N .
.TP
.BI --min-api " N"
Set APK minSdkVersion to
.IR N .
.TP
.BI --target-api " N"
Set APK targetSdkVersion to
.IR N .
.TP
.BI --package " NAME"
Set the Android application package name.
.TP
.BI --label " TEXT"
Set the Android application label.
.TP
.B --keep-temp
Keep the temporary build directory.
.TP
.B --help
Show wrapper help.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B ANDROID_HOME, ANDROID_SDK_ROOT
Android SDK location.
.TP
.B ANDROID_NDK_HOME
Android NDK location.
.TP
.B FBANDROID_PREFIX
Installation prefix used to find the packaged compiler, headers, runtime
libraries, and APK templates.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR fbc (1)
